  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to Conflict Affected Households in Greater Upper Nile, South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM is providing humanitarian assistance to conflict affected households in Greater Upper Nile, vulnerable internally displaced persons (IDPs) in Protection of Civilians (PoC) sites and collective settlements, as well as communities outside of camp settings suffering shocks in South Sudan. In particular, IOM is providing mental health and psychosocial support, protection, water, sanitation and hygiene and shelter (WASH) and non-food Items assistance, as well as camp coordination and camp management and primary health-care services. In addition, in order to respond to COVID-19, IOM is providing critical WASH items, constructing hand washing infrastructure and conducting risk communication activities.</narrative>
  </description>
